race.comment: A relatively large field and tough. MARCH MADNESS (13) needs two scratchings to make the field, but has strong winning claims if he does. Brought strong form to resumption but needed the outing. The 1400m suits with the extra fitness and he tumbles in weight, and that's his edge. Maps for a soft run, and that's a positive as well. GARINION RIGH (6) resumed in the same race and also looked a run short. She'd switched from a Sydney stable, and the extra metres will also advantage. Draws inside and will get every chance. THIRD MASTER (12) has had three starts in the regions since transferring from a NSW stable. Disappointed verses the above pair last time, but is better than that and has to be kept onside. THE GENERAL TALKS (7) has been going along okay, but this is tougher.
